-- Budapest to Buy Back Waterworks From Suez, RWE, Nemzet Reports
-- B y   E d i t h   B a l a z s
-- 2012-03-27T06:52:08Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-03-27/budapest-to-buy-back-waterworks-from-suez-rwe-nemzet-reports.html
Budapest city council authorized
Mayor Istvan Tarlos to repurchase a minority stake in the
Hungarian capitalâ€™s waterworks from  Suez Environnement SA (SEV)  and
RWE Aqua GmBH,  Magyar Nemzet  reported.  The city will pay 15.1 billion forint ($69 million) for the
stake and management rights in Budapest Vizmuvek Zrt., which the
foreign investors purchased for 16.5 billion forint in 1997,
according to the newspaper, which cited Tarlos. The city will
finance the deal from credit and from payments by other  utility
companies , Nemzet said.  Budapest will exercise its option to cancel the contract
should the parties fail to reach an agreement within 90 days,
Tarlos said, according to Nemzet.  To contact the reporter on this story:
